This is the "EULA firewall". It exists because the boundary between what we may
share and what we may not is easy to cross by accident -- one `docker push` of an
image with weights baked in is a redistribution of restricted derived work.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Datasets -- never in this repository
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

SEETHRU trains and evaluates on datasets obtained under separate, signed,
research-only agreements:

  * FaceForensics++ (Roessler et al., ICCV 2019)
    Technical University of Munich.
    Access: https://github.com/ondyari/FaceForensics
    Terms: research use only; redistribution prohibited.

  * Celeb-DF v2 (Li et al., CVPR 2020)
    University at Albany, SUNY.
    Access: https://github.com/yuezunli/celeb-deepfakeforensics
    Terms: research use only; redistribution prohibited.

  * DFDC (Dolhansky et al., 2020) -- optional, evaluation only.
    Terms: per the DFDC dataset licence.

Consequences, which are binding, not advisory:

  * No dataset video, frame, or face crop may be committed to this repository.
    `data/` is gitignored and `.dockerignore` excludes it from all images.
  * Anyone reproducing this work must obtain the data themselves, under their
    own agreement. We provide no copies, mirrors, or links to copies.
  * Each dataset must be cited in any resulting publication. See the papers
    listed above.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. Model weights -- derivative of restricted data
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Weights trained on the datasets above are a derivative work of EULA-restricted
data and inherit those restrictions. Therefore:

  * Trained weights are NOT licensed under Apache-2.0.
  * Trained weights are NOT committed to this repository (`*.pt`, `*.pth`,
    `*.onnx`, `*.ckpt`, `*.safetensors` are gitignored and dockerignored).
  * Trained weights are NOT baked into any public container image. They are
    fetched at runtime from a gated store. See BUILD_PLAN T81.
  * Any release of weights must carry a research-only term, a NOTICE of dataset
    provenance, and a model card. See BUILD_PLAN T84.

If you are unsure whether an artifact may be shared: it may not. Ask first.

